    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CHILD CARE WORKER PLEADS GUILTY</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Wayne Gordon, counselor at Leake &amp; Watts Children's Home in Yonkers, NY, pleads guilty to homicide and assault charges in connection with March 2 automobile accident that killed 17-year-old Crystal Davis (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Wayne Gordon, 36, a child care counselor at the Leake &amp; Watts Children's Home in Yonkers, has pleaded guilty in to criminally negligent homicide and assault in connection with an automobile accident that killed his 17-year-old passenger, Crystal Davis, a student at the residential treatment center. According to the charges, Mr. Gordon was traveling above the speed limit on March 2, when the accident occurred. He faces a maximum of four years in prison when he is sentenced on Oct. 13.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Wayne Gordon, 36, a child care counselor at the Leake &amp; Watts Children's Home in Yonkers, has pleaded guilty in to criminally negligent homicide and assault in connection with an automobile accident that killed his 17-year-old passenger, Crystal Davis, a student at the residential treatment center. According to the charges, Mr. Gordon was traveling above the speed limit on March 2, when the accident occurred. He faces a maximum of four years in prison when he is sentenced on Oct. 13.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
